<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1070,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1178,1203]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Description.</emphasis>
Incomplete individuals; 
<typeStatus box="[632,730,1178,1203]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[748,845,1179,1203]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/6yx0-3nm7" name="Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">MZUSP</collectionCode>
<number box="[845,887,1179,1203]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="387.0">387</number>
) 
<quantity box="[904,993,1179,1203]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1070,1159,1178,1203]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
wide, and 
<number box="[1291,1305,1179,1203]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="8.0">8</number>
chaetigers; 
<typeStatus box="[151,247,1215,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[263,360,1215,1239]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/6yx0-3nm7" name="Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">MZUSP</collectionCode>
<number box="[360,402,1215,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="388.0">388</number>
) 
<quantity box="[417,504,1214,1239]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[577,664,1214,1239]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide, with 
<number box="[799,826,1215,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="11.0">11</number>
chaetigers. Coloration whitish, without pigmentation. Body subcylindrical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1070,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Prostomium quadrangular, slightly wider than long; anterior margin slightly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1243,1286,1311]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[216,1378,205,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[206,1388,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Syllidia amaralae new species. A. Holotype MZUSP 506 with pharynx everted, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, jaws; D. Position of jaws and stylet on proboscis; E. Paratype MZUSP 505, parapodium 4, posterior view; F. Same, parapodium 12, anterior view; G. Supra-acicular heterogomph falciger neurochaetae; H. Sub-acicular heterogomph falciger neurochaetae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231426/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[1228,1243,1287,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Palps located outer to the antennae. Palpophores short, stout; palpostyles globular, slightly longer than palpophores; right one lost on figured 
<typeStatus box="[327,423,1359,1383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[441,506,1358,1383]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,506,1359,1383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Lateral antennae frontal, digitiform, distally rounded, long as palps. Eyes not seen. Nuchal organs not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1070,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Proboscidial diaphragm present. Pharynx muscular occupying the first five chaetigers. Pharynx everted in 
<typeStatus box="[151,252,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">holotype</typeStatus>
, short, smooth, fringed, with about 
<number box="[675,703,1467,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="30.0">30</number>
papillae, small, conical, with ciliate tips (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1267,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[1256,1267,1467,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). First three segments fused, dorsally reduced. Six pairs of tentacular cirri, most lost; cirrophores short, stout; cirrostyles long, moniliform; first pair dorsolateral, second and third pairs lateroventral; first segment with dorsal tentacular cirri larger, complete, reaching chaetiger 
<number box="[558,574,1575,1599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="3.0">3</number>
; ventral cirri slightly shorter than dorsal one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1070,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Parapodia subbiramous. Two straight notoaciculae, not protruding (
<figureCitation box="[959,1023,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[1012,1023,1611,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Notochaetae absent. Most dorsal cirri lost; when present, cirrophore stout, short, cirrostyle long, moniliform, about as long as body width (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1398,1646,1671]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1398,1647,1671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). One neuroacicula distally enlarged, rounded, not protruding (
<figureCitation box="[864,932,1682,1707]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[921,932,1683,1707]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Neuropodial pre- and postchaetal lobes entire, liguliform, both of the same length. Ventral cirri digitiform, distally slender, not annulated, inserted subdistally on parapodial lobe, smaller than dorsal cirri (
<figureCitation box="[825,894,1754,1779]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[883,894,1755,1779]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Ventral adhesive papillae paired, rounded, situated postero-laterally to parapodia (
<figureCitation box="[590,652,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[642,652,1791,1815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B–D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1070,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Neurochaetae about 
<number box="[430,458,1826,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="15.0">15</number>
heterogomph falcigers per bundle; blade medium-sized to long, with a long basal spur (prolonged teeth), one-third as long as blade. Supra-acicular neurochaetae bidentate, with unequal teeth, hooded (hood arises from inferior teeth) (
<figureCitation box="[541,607,1898,1923]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[596,607,1899,1923]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E); subacicular ones without hood, unidentate, with teeth stouter, and a basal arista, finer (
<figureCitation box="[367,434,1934,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,209,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[265,1321,195,1557]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Micropodarke pleijeli new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 388, anterior region, right dorsolateral view; B. Same, parapodium 11, left side view; C. Same, parapodium 11, right side view; D. Parapodium 6 showing the ventral adhesive papilla (vap), right side view; E. Supra-acicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, with hood and spur; F. Subacicular heterogomph bidentate falciger, without hood; G. Neurochaeta elongated and slender." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[423,434,1935,1959]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F), and 
<number box="[530,571,1935,1959]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
longer neurochaetae, slender, unidentate, without hood, in central position (
