<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="272" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1734,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the key to species, 
<taxonomicName box="[583,702,1734,1758]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pleijeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[583,702,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">M. pleijeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,778,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[712,778,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is nearest of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1983" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1983" box="[940,1386,1734,1759]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis box="[940,1078,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">M. trilobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[1089,1386,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1983) Die Polychaeten der antiborealen Sudkuste Australiens (zwischen Albany im Westen und Ceduna im Osten). Teil 10. In: Hartmann-Schroder, G. and Gerd Hartmann. Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 81, 7 - 62." type="journal article" year="1983">
Hartmann-Schröder, 
<number box="[1327,1386,1735,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by having antennae thin, tapered, and palpostyle medially swollen, blunt instead the antennae are thick, blunt, and the palpostyle is medially swollen, tapered. 
<taxonomicName box="[791,1039,1806,1830]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pleijeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[791,1039,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">Micropodarke pleijeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1049,1116,1806,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1049,1116,1806,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hessle, 1925" authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1925" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[1331,1436,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">M. dubia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hessle" box="[159,307,1842,1867]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" refString="Hessle, C. (1925) Einiges uber die Hesioniden und die Stellung der Gattung Ancistrosyllis. Arkiv for Zoologi, 17 A, 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1925">
Hessle, 
<number box="[249,307,1842,1867]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by lacking eyes, having a pharynx with more papillae, and by the neurochaetal features. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" refString="Pleijel, F. &amp; Rouse, G. W. (2005) A revision of Micropodarke (Psamathini, Hesionidae, Polychaeta). Journal of Natural History, 39, 1313 - 1325. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400020129" type="journal article" year="2005">
Pleijel and Rouse (
<number box="[235,294,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<number box="[434,504,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25</number>
elongated ciliated papillae, while 
<taxonomicName box="[886,1001,1878,1902]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pleijeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[886,1001,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">M. pleijeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1008,1070,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1008,1070,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has about 
<number box="[1190,1221,1879,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="30.0">30</number>
; also indicated 
<number box="[1394,1436,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
neurochaetae in median position having 
<number box="[609,652,1915,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
basal prolonged teeth or “spurs”; however 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1260,1915,1939]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pleijeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1144,1260,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">M. pleijeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1268,1332,1914,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1268,1332,1914,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has only one spur. Besides, the supra-acicular neurochaetae are bidentate, hooded, and the subacicular ones are unidentate, without hood.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after Dr. Fredrik Pleijel for his contributions to the study of the polychaetes in general, especially in recognition of his many, fine publications on hesionid systematics.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="273" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">
